# Supabase database types

- Always use the generated types from `supabase/database.types.ts` when creating
  or using a Supabase client.
- Do not hand-write table/row types that duplicate the generated schema.
- If types are missing or outdated, run `npm run db:sync` to pull schema and
  regenerate types.
- If `db:sync` is slow or fails, prefer `npm run db:types` (or
  `npx supabase gen types typescript --linked`) after ensuring the project is
  linked via `npx supabase link --project-ref <ref>`.
- After regeneration, update imports to use:
  `import type { Database } from "@/supabase/database.types";`
